From: Pavel Polikashin <polikashin@celestialtech.io>
Date: Tue, 11 Nov 2025 22:00:38 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] feat: Implement queue-based file opening to fix network
 interface connection resets
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Added event-based request queue system for file/open endpoint that decouples
network responses from Provider operations, resolving [Errno 54] Connection
reset by peer errors. Network callbacks now return immediately with request_id
while file opening happens asynchronously on main thread via EventFrameEnd.

Changes:
- Add FileOpenRequest queue infrastructure with thread-safe management
- Replace file/open with queue-based endpoint returning pending status
- Add file/open/status endpoint for progress tracking
- Implement processFileOpenQueue() called every frame on main thread
- Subscribe to EventFrameEnd for periodic queue processing

This implements Solution 1 (Event-Based Response Queue) from FILE_OPEN_ANALYSIS.md,
achieving the primary goal of preventing connection resets without requiring
ImHex core modifications.

